The paper deals with the problem of community detection and matrix completion, which are both topics in machine learning and data analysis. The use of similarity graphs and stochastic block models also suggests a focus on graph-based methods, which are commonly studied in the subfield of machine learning known as graph-based learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
